 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-17g6","title":"Enhance Playwright reporter with phase events","description":"## Priority 3: Enhance Playwright Reporter with Phase Events

### Current Issue
The Playwright JSONL reporter (tests/e2e/reporters/jsonl-reporter.ts) emits run_start/test_start/test_end/run_end but lacks phase_start/phase_end support for granular test tracking.

### Required Changes

1. **Hook into test.step() as phase boundaries:**

```typescript
// In jsonl-reporter.ts

onStepBegin(test: TestCase, result: TestResult, step: TestStep) {
  if (step.category === 'test.step') {
    this.emitEvent({
      event: 'phase_start',
      phase: {
        name: this.slugify(step.title),
        description: step.title
      },
      test: this.getTestInfo(test)
    });
    this.stepStartTimes.set(step, Date.now());
  }
}

onStepEnd(test: TestCase, result: TestResult, step: TestStep) {
  if (step.category === 'test.step') {
    const startTime = this.stepStartTimes.get(step) || Date.now();
    const duration_ms = Date.now() - startTime;

    this.emitEvent({
      event: 'phase_end',
      phase: {
        name: this.slugify(step.title),
        description: step.title
      },
      duration_ms,
      test: this.getTestInfo(test)
    });
  }
}
```

2. **Update spec files to use test.step():**

```typescript
// Example in encryption/password-flow.spec.ts
test('encrypts and decrypts content', async ({ page }) => {
  await test.step('Load encrypted page', async () => {
    await page.goto('/encrypted.html');
  });

  await test.step('Enter password', async () => {
    await page.fill('#password', 'secret');
    await page.click('#submit');
  });

  await test.step('Verify decrypted content', async () => {
    await expect(page.locator('.content')).toBeVisible();
  });
});
```

### Files to Modify
- tests/e2e/reporters/jsonl-reporter.ts

### Files to Update (optional - for better phase coverage)
- tests/e2e/encryption/password-flow.spec.ts
- tests/e2e/interactivity/search.spec.ts
- Other complex spec files

### Testing Requirements (CRITICAL)

1. **Unit tests for reporter (tests/e2e/reporters/jsonl-reporter.test.ts):**
```typescript
import { JsonlReporter } from './jsonl-reporter';

describe('JsonlReporter', () => {
  it('emits phase_start on step begin', () => {
    const reporter = new JsonlReporter();
    const events: any[] = [];
    reporter.emitEvent = (e) => events.push(e);

    reporter.onStepBegin(mockTest, mockResult, mockStep);

    expect(events).toContainEqual(expect.objectContaining({
      event: 'phase_start',
      phase: expect.objectContaining({ name: expect.any(String) })
    }));
  });

  it('emits phase_end with duration on step end', () => {
    const reporter = new JsonlReporter();
    const events: any[] = [];
    reporter.emitEvent = (e) => events.push(e);

    reporter.onStepBegin(mockTest, mockResult, mockStep);
    // Simulate some time passing
    reporter.onStepEnd(mockTest, mockResult, mockStep);

    expect(events).toContainEqual(expect.objectContaining({
      event: 'phase_end',
      duration_ms: expect.any(Number)
    }));
  });
});
```

2. **Integration test:**
```bash
# Run Playwright tests and check for phase events
npx playwright test encryption/password-flow.spec.ts
cat test-results/e2e/playwright_*.jsonl | jq 'select(.event == "phase_start" or .event == "phase_end")'
# Should show phase events
```

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Phase events emitted for test.step() calls
- [ ] Duration calculated correctly (> 0ms)
- [ ] Phase names are slugified for consistency
- [ ] Events follow existing schema format
- [ ] Unit tests for reporter pass
- [ ] Integration test shows phase events in JSONL","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T17:21:37.332870142Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T22:26:05.835893885Z","closed_at":"2026-01-27T22:26:05.835823574Z","close_reason":"Already implemented - jsonl-reporter.ts has onStepBegin/onStepEnd methods (lines 260-287) that emit phase_start/phase_end events for test.step() calls","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-17i8","title":"P4.4: Local Preview Server","description":"# Local Preview Server

**Parent Phase:** Phase 4: Wizard & Deployment
**Depends On:** P4.1 (Interactive Wizard)
**Duration:** 1-2 days

## Goal

Implement a local HTTP server for previewing exported archives before deployment, with proper COOP/COEP headers.

## Technical Approach

### CLI Command

cass pages --preview <DIR>
cass pages --preview ./cass-pages-export/site

### Features

1. Serve Static Files
   - All files from site/ directory
   - Proper MIME types

2. Add COOP/COEP Headers
   - Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
   - Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp

3. Live URL Display
   Preview available at: http://localhost:8080
   Press Ctrl+C to stop

4. Auto-Open Browser (optional)
   --open flag to launch default browser

### Implementation Options

Option A: Use tiny_http crate
- Lightweight, simple
- ~100 lines of code

Option B: Use axum/actix
- More features
- Heavier dependencies

Recommend Option A for minimal footprint.

### MIME Type Handling

.html  -> text/html
.js    -> application/javascript
.wasm  -> application/wasm
.json  -> application/json
.css   -> text/css
.bin   -> application/octet-stream

### Exit Criteria

1. Server starts on available port
2. COOP/COEP headers set
3. All file types served correctly
4. Graceful shutdown on Ctrl+C
5. Error message if port in use","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T01:38:14.255861418Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-07T06:01:36.971235356Z","closed_at":"2026-01-07T06:01:36.971235356Z","close_reason":"Duplicate of coding_agent_session_search-regb","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-17i8","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-9cby","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-11T06:20:53Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"coding_agent_session_search-17i8","depends_on_id":"coding_agent_session_search-rzst","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-11T06:20:53Z","created_by":"import"}]}
